properties.sfomuseum:notes_library: A collection of extracted and photocopied articles, reprints, printed lectures, etc., by Albert F. Zahm, prepared for his own use from a number of different sources and publications. Zahm's preface for v. 1 notes: "The five [volumes], composed in convenient page sizes, comprise articles published in the period 1885 to 1942 inclusive. As yet no steps have been taken to publish them in book form." Zahm's collected papers were eventually published by the University of Notre Dame in 1950.Typewritten t.p.'s, with place and date of compilation given as Washington, D.C., 1942, are inserted at the front of each v.Vol. 3 has added t.p.: Some papers on aerodynamics prepared at the U.S. Navy Aerodynamical Laboratory, communicated to the U.S. National Advisory Committee for Aeronautics by Albert Francis Zahm. Washington, D.C., Dec., 1929.Includes bibliographical references.
